         Thanks for the comments above which suggest to me that more testing is still required.</P><P>I have cast DoTs on myself and on mobs and timed them to the second using a desktop timer. I saw the activation message for the extended affliction item. There is no doubt in my mind that they lasted EXACTLY the same amount of time with or without the focus. HOWEVER this was roughly a week after focus items were introduced an dit may just be that they didn't have them working properly then. I am pretty sure it is the same now however since I think I would have noticed if duration increased 20% (20% of say a dooming dark being a pretty noticable 18 seconds (normal duration is 90 seconds)). </P><P>That said i'll test it again now and see how it goes - I had hoped someone here might have one of those programs that measures DPS by data capture to really see what is going on but hey - back to in the field testing. </P><P>Falrinth</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
