        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Extended Affliction does not affect initial DPS (how much you do until oom), but it does affect Sustained DPS (how much DPS you can maintain indefinitly).</P><P>It works on any spell considered "detrimental" to the mob. I.E. any spell that is harmful and stays on the mob more than one tic, so charm, snare, slow, DoTs, debuffs etc. are all extended.</P><P>I have a coldain military bracer and always keep it on despite the stats.</P><P><EMBED src="http://www.geocities.com/wraithcf/includes/swf/sig2.swf" loop=false menu=false quality=best WIDTH=300 HEIGHT=150 TYPE="application/x-shockwave-flash"</EMBED></P><P>Edited by - Ailaell on 09/30/2002  12:27:53<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

