        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         I’ve posted my thoughts on Extended Affliction before, but I’ll post it again since this seems a more appropriate place for it.</P><P>I think Extended Affliction should be replaced with Enhanced Affliction. I find that in most cases (Except soloing if I want to sit and watch mobs slowly die while my exp bar sometimes twitches a pixel.) that mobs die before 70% of my DOTS worn off. I’m losing a LOT of damage that way and my mana efficiency goes out the window when that happens.</P><P>Enhanced Affliction should make DOTS do their FULL damage in less time. That would make it something I can use in every day life. (raids, exp groups, item hunting, soloing, questing etc.)</P><P>I would personally like to see our DOTS do their damage in 20-30% less time with items like this. That doesn’t shave an insane amount of time off your damage, and mobs will still often die before your dots complete, but it will increase our efficiency/DPS.</P><P>I would also throw in a Class AA skill that would allow you to “Crit” with a DOT, allowing it to do it’s full damage on impact. (3%-7% chance perhaps.)</P><P>That’s what I would pursue if I were in the developers chair anyway.</P><P><BR><img src="http://www.jackntracie.com/images/gojirax.jpg" border=0><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
